<subSubSection id="A7E16578FF9B897E4987C129FC49F328" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EF4436F3FF9B897E4987C129FC49F328" blockId="11.[151,1437,448,1901]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="DD8FEAE1FF9B897E4987C129FEAEF302" bold="true" box="[196,346,1837,1863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="28FB4D70FF9B897E4B16C12AFD20F302" box="[597,724,1838,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Blissidae" genus="Macropes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis id="DD8FEAE1FF9B897E4B16C12AFD20F302" box="[597,724,1838,1863]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Latin adjective, in reference to the pronotum being relatively elongated, and the shape of lateral margins is peculiar, too.
</paragraph>
